In this statement, President Obama commends Nigeria for its commitment to democratic principles during the recent elections. He praises President Goodluck Jonathan for conceding the election and congratulating President-Elect Muhammadu Buhari. President Obama expresses his willingness to work with both leaders and urges them to call on their supporters to respect the election outcomes and focus on unifying the country. He also recognizes Nigeria's Independent National Election Commission (INEC) and its Chairman, Attahiru Jega, for conducting a largely peaceful and orderly vote. President Obama extends congratulations to the people of Nigeria and looks forward to working with the newly-elected government on shared priorities.